	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />like previously said. Mario/Duck Hunt most of the time came with the chips on-die (nickednamed glop-tops).
<br />
<br />I personally have three M/DH carts, one of which is this way. I also have a Mario/Duck Hunt/Track Meet cart with glop-tops ironically enough.
<br />
<br />Easiest way I've found to get versions without die is to visit a physical game shop and purchase the heavier ones...This is also a good tatic to get joint boards for famicart conversions, since they'd weigh the most (by experience they also seem to be uneven too).
<br />
<br />ed: typo/homonym

		

